**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Description:** The image shows the front fender of a white vehicle.

**Location of Damage:** The damage is located on the lower portion of the front fender, near the wheel well area.

**Type of Damage:** The damage appears to be a scratch or scrape, likely caused by an impact with another object. The paint has been chipped away, revealing the underlying metal beneath. There are visible streaks and smears of dirt or debris, indicating that the damage occurred recently.

**Additional Notes:**
- The damage seems to be localized and does not appear to have affected the structural integrity of the fender.
- The surrounding area of the fender looks relatively undamaged.

**Conclusion:** The vehicle has sustained minor surface damage to the front fender, which can be repaired through painting and touch-up work. No significant structural damage is apparent from the image provided.
